# Border-Radius Standard

All cards, panels, buttons, and interactive elements use a **single design token**: `rounded-card`.

The value is defined in `app/globals.css`:
```css
--radius-card: 0.125rem; /* 2px — subtle, near-square; matches Hero accordion panels */
```

And registered in `tailwind.config.ts`:
```ts
borderRadius: { card: 'var(--radius-card)' }
```

## Rules

- ✅ Use `rounded-card` for all cards, panels, buttons, icon rings, nav buttons, dropdowns, and modal surfaces
- ✅ Use `rounded-b-card` / `rounded-t-card` etc. for partial rounding on attached elements (e.g. mobile menu dropdowns)
- ✅ `rounded-full` is allowed only for pills, avatars, progress bars, and circular elements
- ❌ Never hardcode `rounded-sm`, `rounded-md`, `rounded-lg`, `rounded-xl`, `rounded-[Npx]`, or `rounded-[Nrem]` on card/button surfaces
- ❌ Never use different radius values on different components — consistency is enforced via the CSS variable

## Changing the radius

To update the radius site-wide, change **only** the CSS variable in `globals.css`:
```css
--radius-card: 0.25rem; /* change here → propagates everywhere */
```

Do not change individual component classes.

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
<div className="rounded-card border bg-white">...</div>
<button className="rounded-card px-4 py-2">Submit</button>
<div className="rounded-b-card border-t">Mobile dropdown</div>

// ❌ Wrong
<div className="rounded-lg border bg-white">...</div>
<button className="rounded-md px-4 py-2">Submit</button>
<div className="rounded-b-[11px] border-t">Mobile dropdown</div>
```
